trans-unit.source: Uninstall Visual Studio 2015
trans-unit.target: Uninstall Visual Studio 2015

trans-unit.source: This page walks you through uninstalling Visual Studio, our integrated suite of productivity tools for developers.
trans-unit.target: This page walks you through uninstalling Visual Studio, our integrated suite of productivity tools for developers.

trans-unit.source: To uninstall Visual Studio by using the "standard" uninstallation method
trans-unit.target: To uninstall Visual Studio by using the "standard" uninstallation method

trans-unit.source: In Control Panel, on the Programs and Features page, choose the product edition that you want to uninstall, and then choose Change.
trans-unit.target: In Control Panel, on the Programs and Features page, choose the product edition that you want to uninstall, and then choose Change.

trans-unit.source: In the Setup wizard, choose Uninstall, choose Yes, and then follow the remaining instructions in the wizard.
trans-unit.target: In the Setup wizard, choose Uninstall, choose Yes, and then follow the remaining instructions in the wizard.

trans-unit.source:
<div class="section">
This standard, or default method will leave some items behind that your first installation of Visual Studio originally installed (for example, the Microsoft .NET Framework, Microsoft Visual C++ Redistributables, Microsoft SQL Server, etc.).
trans-unit.target:
<div class="section">
This standard, or default method will leave some items behind that your first installation of Visual Studio originally installed (for example, the Microsoft .NET Framework, Microsoft Visual C++ Redistributables, Microsoft SQL Server, etc.).

trans-unit.source: We leave these installed because many other applications depend on them.
trans-unit.target: We leave these installed because many other applications depend on them.

trans-unit.source: However, if you want to remove them too, select their entry in Programs and Features, and then remove each individually.
trans-unit.target: However, if you want to remove them too, select their entry in Programs and Features, and then remove each individually.

trans-unit.source: To uninstall Visual Studio and all other related files (that is, to uninstall almost everything)
trans-unit.target: To uninstall Visual Studio and all other related files (that is, to uninstall almost everything)

trans-unit.source:
<div class="section">
Locate the Visual Studio .exe file (for example, locate "vs_enterprise.exe").
trans-unit.target:
<div class="section">
Locate the Visual Studio .exe file (for example, locate "vs_enterprise.exe").

trans-unit.source: Note
trans-unit.target: Note

trans-unit.source: The file should be in a subfolder of "%ProgramData%\Package Cache", for example: C:\ProgramData\Package Cache\{37e19555-e88d-4aed-9d42-82d0784d2b79}\vs_enterprise.exe
trans-unit.target: The file should be in a subfolder of "%ProgramData%\Package Cache", for example: C:\ProgramData\Package Cache\{37e19555-e88d-4aed-9d42-82d0784d2b79}\vs_enterprise.exe

trans-unit.source:
<div class="section">
Run the .exe file by using the /uninstall /force command-line parameters.
trans-unit.target:
<div class="section">
Run the .exe file by using the /uninstall /force command-line parameters.

trans-unit.source: For example, run: vs_enterprise.exe /uninstall /force
trans-unit.target: For example, run: vs_enterprise.exe /uninstall /force

trans-unit.source:
<div class="section">
This will remove Visual Studio and most of the core components that are left behind in a default uninstallation.
trans-unit.target:
<div class="section">
This will remove Visual Studio and most of the core components that are left behind in a default uninstallation.

trans-unit.source: However, it will not remove all of the additional content that Visual Studio add-ons and extensions can install (for example, Visual Studio updates, and other optional components).
trans-unit.target: However, it will not remove all of the additional content that Visual Studio add-ons and extensions can install (for example, Visual Studio updates, and other optional components).

trans-unit.source: Alternatively, you can use the "Total Uninstaller" tool to remove everything that Visual Studio or updates to Visual Studio might have installed.
trans-unit.target: Alternatively, you can use the "Total Uninstaller" tool to remove everything that Visual Studio or updates to Visual Studio might have installed.

trans-unit.source: That is, any version of Visual Studio 2013 or later.
trans-unit.target: That is, any version of Visual Studio 2013 or later.

trans-unit.source: To find out more, see the Visual Studio Uninstaller tool on GitHub.
trans-unit.target: To find out more, see the Visual Studio Uninstaller tool on GitHub.

trans-unit.source: To uninstall Visual Studio in silent or passive modes (that is, to uninstall from source)
trans-unit.target: To uninstall Visual Studio in silent or passive modes (that is, to uninstall from source)

trans-unit.source: On the computer where Visual Studio is installed, open the Windows command prompt.
trans-unit.target: On the computer where Visual Studio is installed, open the Windows command prompt.

trans-unit.source: Enter the following parameters: DVDRoot \ [/norestart]/uninstall
trans-unit.target: Enter the following parameters: DVDRoot \ [/norestart]/uninstall

trans-unit.source: To roll back to a previous version or release of Visual Studio
trans-unit.target: To roll back to a previous version or release of Visual Studio

trans-unit.source:
<div class="section">
Uninstall Visual Studio by using any of the methods listed in this topic.
trans-unit.target:
<div class="section">
Uninstall Visual Studio by using any of the methods listed in this topic.

trans-unit.source: Tip
trans-unit.target: Tip

trans-unit.source: <tr> <td>Uninstalling a current release of Visual Studio (or a Visual Studio Update) and then installing a previous release might not work as expected.
trans-unit.target: <tr> <td>Uninstalling a current release of Visual Studio (or a Visual Studio Update) and then installing a previous release might not work as expected.

trans-unit.source: The outcome depends on the which version or release of Visual Studio you have installed, which versions of its components are installed, which products are installed that might have dependencies either the Visual Studio release or its components, and finally, on which earlier Visual Studio version you plan to install or reinstall.
trans-unit.target: The outcome depends on the which version or release of Visual Studio you have installed, which versions of its components are installed, which products are installed that might have dependencies either the Visual Studio release or its components, and finally, on which earlier Visual Studio version you plan to install or reinstall.

trans-unit.source: Because of all these variables, a standard uninstall will often leave components behind that might not work with previous Visual Studio versions or releases.
trans-unit.target: Because of all these variables, a standard uninstall will often leave components behind that might not work with previous Visual Studio versions or releases.

trans-unit.source: Therefore, for best results, we recommend using the Visual Studio Uninstaller tool.
trans-unit.target: Therefore, for best results, we recommend using the Visual Studio Uninstaller tool.

trans-unit.source: Install or reinstall the earlier version of Visual Studio that you want to use.
trans-unit.target: Install or reinstall the earlier version of Visual Studio that you want to use.

trans-unit.source:
<div class="section">
Even if you install a previous version of Visual Studio, the Setup program might still try to use a newer version or release if one is available.
trans-unit.target:
<div class="section">
Even if you install a previous version of Visual Studio, the Setup program might still try to use a newer version or release if one is available.

trans-unit.source: For more detailed information, see the How to: Install a Specific Release of Visual Studio topic.
trans-unit.target: For more detailed information, see the How to: Install a Specific Release of Visual Studio topic.
